The paper deals with a communication problem in a network, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The use of combinatorial properties of the graph to show intractability suggests that the paper may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The study of efficient data exchange schemes may also place the paper in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories.
